<H1 ALIGN="CENTER">Help the VMG</H1>
<B>Don't panic!</B> I am not closing down the <A HREF="/vmg">VMG</A>
nor am I starting to charge for the service it provides! However,
there are some areas where I could do with some help:
<UL>
<LI>I would like to have at least one, but preferably more, stable
backup sites. Right now if anything happens to me then the <A HREF="/vmg">VMG</A> is gone. I don't want that to happen - I think
that preserving continuity is vital. This is the important item, the
others are idle dreaming!</LI>
<LI>It would be rather good to get the <A HREF="/vmg">VMG</A> its own
domain name and move it to its own machine. This costs money and I
dont have any to spare and I am not asking for yours! (I am not even
sure I would be allowed to take it even if you offered it to me!) I
did try to get one of the computer companies to sponsor the site, but
no dice there. (Being in the UK and not being a high profile site with
millions of hits tends to rule you out of the sponsorship game)
Ideas welcome.
<LI>If I could get more resources somehow, I would like to extend the
services provided by the <A HREF="/vmg">VMG</A> and provide some form
of archiving. I have lots of ideas....</LI>
</UL>
If you think you can help or have some suggestions then <A
HREF="mailto:lindsay.Marshall@newcastle.ac.uk">e-mail me</A>.
