<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>The Virtual Memorial Garden - New Features</TITLE>
<LINKS REV="made" HREF="Lindsay.Marshall@newcastle.ac.uk">
</HEAD><BODY BACKGROUND="/Images/Bg/sandston.gif">
<P ALIGN="CENTER">
<A HREF="http://www.cs.umd.edu/services/roget/entries/505.html"><IMG
SRC="/Images/Misc/vmg2.gif"
HEIGHT="36" WIDTH="437" ALT="The Virtual Memorial Garden" Border ="0"></A><BR>
<H1 ALIGN="CENTER">New Features</H1>
I have introduced three new features that I hope you will find useful.
<OL>
<LI>If you click on the bronze button next to each memorial you will
be taken to a page, specific to each memorial, where you can record
your thoughts about the memorial.
<P></LI>
<LI> You will notice that on these special memorial pages that the name
of the person is shown as a link. If you save this link you can 
directly return to the place in the VMG where their memorial is stored
without having to search through the pages.
<P></LI>
<LI>Pet memorials have been rearranged and also have all the individual
memorial pages and unique anchors.</LI>
</OL>
<P>
Please let me know of any problems you encounter and of any ways that
I can improve these services.</P>
<P ALIGN="RIGHT">
<I><A HREF="mailto:Lindsay.Marshall@newcastle.ac.uk">Lindsay Marshall</A></I>
<P ALIGN="CENTER">
<IMG SRC="/Images/Lines/g200.gif" ALT="" WIDTH="200" HEIGHT="4"></P>
</BODY></HTML>
